<h3>
    Seasonal Patterns and Fishing Times
</h3>
<p>
    Brown trout in Oregon behave differently throughout the year. Understanding their seasonal rhythms can increase your success:
</p>
<ul>
    <li>
        <strong>Spring:</strong> Active after ice melt; feed aggressively on aquatic insects and minnows.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Summer:</strong> Seek shade and deeper water; early morning and dusk are best.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Fall:</strong> Peak season; spawning instincts make browns more aggressive.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Winter:</strong> Activity slows, but some trophy browns still strike.
    </li>
</ul>
<p>
    Prime months: <strong>April-May</strong> and <strong>September-October.</strong>
</p>
<h3>
    Essential Gear for Brown Trout Fishing
</h3>
<p>
    To target brown trout effectively near Eugene, you’ll need quality gear:
</p>
<ul>
    <li>
        <strong>Rods:</strong> 5-7 weight fly rods or ultralight spinning rods
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Reels:</strong> Smooth drag system, especially for large river browns
    </li>
    <li>
