</p>
<ul>
    <li>
        <strong>Live Bait:</strong> Nightcrawlers and minnows fished under floats or drifted
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Lures:</strong> Spinners, spoons, and crankbaits mimic prey effectively
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Flies:</strong> Streamers, nymphs, and dry flies during hatches
    </li>
</ul>
<p>
    Presentation is key—long casts and subtle retrievals work best in clear water.
</p>
